
[1]epiphonema

   EPIPHONE'MA, [Gr. exclamation, to cry out.] In oratory, an exclamation;
   an ecphonesis; a vehement utterance of the voice to express strong
   passion, in a sentence not closely connected with the general strain of
   the discourse; as, O mournful day! Miserable fate! Admirable clemency!
     __________________________________________________________________

